Replace the previous approach of skipping ACPI measurement (old patch 0004)
with a complete ACPI semantic firewall that:

1. Discards ALL host-provided AML tables (DSDT/SSDT/PSDT/OSDT) — prevents
   BadAML attacks and eliminates host-dependent RTMR values
2. Skips measurement of ALL QEMU fw_cfg ACPI blobs — non-AML tables
   (FADT, MADT, MCFG, etc.) are host-generated and vary with hardware
   config (MADT changes with -smp count, DMAR with vIOMMU). Measuring
   them creates host-dependent RTMRs with no security benefit.
2. Installs a hardcoded, build-time-compiled DSDT (CvmDsdt.asl) with:
   - Static q35 topology: PCI0, ISA bridge, COM1, HPET, GPE0
   - Full 128-entry _PRT routing tables (PIC + APIC mode)
   - _OSC that grants PME/AER/PCIeCapability, denies hotplug
   - Sentinel values for PCI MMIO windows (patched at runtime)
3. Validates MMIO isolation invariants before patching:
   - 32-bit window must exist and fit in UINT32 range
   - 64-bit window (optional) must be above 4GiB
   - Per-HOB interval overlap check proves MMIO ∩ RAM = ∅
5. Measures the hardcoded DSDT (before sentinel patching) for deterministic
   RTMR attestation — the only ACPI measurement in the entire fw_cfg path

New files:
  CvmDsdt.asl      — Static q35 DSDT template (compiled by iasl at build time)
  CvmDsdtRecon.c/h  — Reconstructor: patch, validate, measure, install

Modified files:
  QemuFwCfgAcpi.c       — Hook points to skip/discard host AML, call reconstructor
  DxeAcpiPlatformLib.inf — Add sources, HobLib, PCI MMIO PCDs

Signed-off-by: Kawiri <patches@kawiri.ai>
